jvmArgs might still be allowed. I just noticed a potential issue with tests. It turns out they shouldn't contain `$` in names. Also, keeping tests outside the library's packages is essential, and I think we might be mixing them. Lastly, I need to check resource bundle registration for potential Native Image issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reflecting on Resource Bundle Handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to improve the robustness of the fallback line 481. If a resource exists only in `en_US`, I can use `ResourceBundle.getBundle(base, Locale.ENGLISH)`, but I wonder if it might still fallback to the root if the root is absent—which is good. However, if a previous `devMode` cleared the resource bundle cache, I might not face any issues.\\n\\nNow, if the test order doesn’t invoke the fallback first, the cache may still include `en_US`, and that could be tricky. The `DefaultI18N.cacheBundle` potentially caches the bundle by `rb.getLocale()`, which raises a question about language properties. I might want to assert that the locale is correct. Also, generating the test resource package could help, but I'm unsure if I’ll need to add an underscore in the path.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Resource Control Changes**\\n\\nI’m thinking that I might not need a public class for resource control after all. I also wonder if I should update the `build.gradle` to include `--initialize-at-build-time`, but I’m leaning towards no on that. Then there’s the generic test — it doesn’t seem to be one-to-one, so maybe I should delete it if it's only active for the class. Plus, I need to check the line length for formatting issues, particularly for a string that’s 93 characters long.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying dynamic-access mapping**\\n\\nI'm trying to make sense of this one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files. It seems like if there are two dynamic classes, then there should be corresponding test files for each, right? It feels like the existing placeholder isn’t mapping correctly, which makes the whole testing process confusing. I wonder how to ensure that everything aligns properly, so I'll need to think through how to address this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering active class tests**\\n\\nI think we should focus solely on the active class, avoiding any mention of I18N$1. So, let’s prioritize creating tests for the active dynamic-access class in a dedicated file. I need to finalize a concise summary without running any tests yet. Plus, it’s important to mention the build arguments involved as they play a significant role. I'll make sure to keep everything organized as I wrap this up!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.codehaus.plexus.i18n.DefaultI18N`.\n\nChanges:\n- Replaced placeholder test with dedicated public test class:\n  - `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-i18n/1.0-beta-7/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_i18n/DefaultI18NTest.java`\n- Added test resource bundle:\n  - `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-i18n/1.0-beta-7/src/test/resources/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_i18n/PlexusMessages_en_US.properties`\n- Updated `build.gradle` to open `java.util` for the dev-mode ResourceBundle cache reflection path:\n  - JVM test arg: `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`\n  - Native image build arg: `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`\n\nCoverage intent:\n- `ResourceBundle#getBundle(String)` via `PLEXUS_DEV_MODE=true`\n- `Class#getDeclaredField`, `Field#get`, `Class#getDeclaredMethod`, `Method#invoke` via DefaultI18N dev-mode cache clearing\n- `ResourceBundle#getBundle(String, Locale)` via normal explicit-locale lookup\n- `getBundleIgnoreException` fallback path via locale/default-country fallback\n\nI did not run tests, per instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_068f54522d4aae56016a0312dfa9b48195b58fd71473709a2f\",\"phase\":\"final